review_title: Not my taste, but the art is fun
one_reviews_text: I just didn't like all of the butt stuff. Also that main little guy was giving me bad vibes, i would have liked it more if the were less emphasis on him. Props to the artists though it looks really nice and the wavy arms are fun

review_title: PARTY OF ONE, PARTY OF ONE
one_reviews_text: YESSSSSSSS, that was fun.  Get's the juices flowing and puts a stupid grin on your face.  I might start my day like this each morning!
So incredibly fun, this will be how I introduce everyone to the Rift from now on. Well done!
and they love me
best 3 dollars spent on vr
just try it

I got this bundled with another game and wasn't sure what to expect. One of the weirder things I've enjoyed on the Rift - but enjoy it I did. After about 30 seconds I was unable to wipe the grin off my face and there are parts that make me laugh out loud every time. I'm sure it's not for everybody, but it just might be for you.
so much fun in this experience - it's a bizarre trippy thing, but enjoyable. Hard to stop yourself drumming.
Best start in the day! Best title to show to people new to VR games :)
Amazing little music video for a really catchy tune. Great way to show off how good VR can be. YOU GOTTA GET IT!

I love these things.  They are such good quick experiences and leave you so happy.  So good to share this kind of things with friends that will appreciate some joyful,funny art and music.  More more more please!

Yes, it is short. But I have probably experienced it 50 times since I purchased it months ago and it never fails to make me smile and send chills down my spine as I dance around like an idiot. The interactive aspect is perfect.

Nice little VR experience, especially for anybody new to VR.  Catchy little tune and you get to be silly.  However, there's no real gameplay element.  You can sit and do nothing or you can dance along (assuming you don't trip over wires).  Just needs more to justify the price tag.
I don't know what I was expecting but the reviews were good. I feel like they must be fans. This was about the cheapest, lamest productive yet.
Considering the other reviews, I am not impressed. Oh well - price is right.
Wow, this is so wonderful.  It's just the escape I needed.  Thank you thank you, best VR music video ever... I would like to go live at that place for a while <3

review_title: Not bad, kind of fun, too short
one_reviews_text: Could be 5 stars if it was free. Doesn't worth paying for it, in my opinion.

This is definitely greater than the sum of its parts. It's the eye-contact and the little interactions that sell it, you feel like you're there and part of the world, with some sort of relationship to these odd little folk.  The sense of fun is infectious.  For my taste, you could still take one more big step away from the hip-thrusting little men, and go further towards psychadelic Yellow Submarine surrealism.

I actually bought this game on Steam and AGAIN in the Oculus Store, just because I thought the developers of this deserved more of my money. It really is that joyous. Sure, it's only 3 minutes, but it's 3 minutes you'll want to dive back into again and again. I've spent more time dancing to this song than I have playing 90% of the games in my VR library. It's cheaper than an ice cream cone, and you will love it.
Couldn't stop smiling
worth it

Basically, an animated music video. Not the most spectacular graphics I've ever seen, not the greatest animation I've ever watched, and not the most fantastic song I've ever heard. It's over-hyped, and the WIRED quote is ridiculous. I personally liked Squarepusher on mobile better.

review_title: my day went from bad to great
one_reviews_text: wasn't having the best day ever... decided to just try this out.. i mean ya only live once right... and boom i could not stop laughing.. everything was great. possibly the best vr dance party ever.. this game puts you in a place where you can dance ya butt off and be free and be yourself without a care...

Wonderfully silly and playful experience, you can't avoid feeling happy! Also, it's one of the first apps that actually gives you a body.

Keep these music experiences coming, we need more of them!

Same characters of "Butt: The VR experience" introducing a funny song making use of a slippery virtual body with great coreography and a psicodelic scenery. But, IMHO, it is only one song with great visuals, and for than reason, too expensive.
Well a short music animation, and yes a bit over hyped
Funny music video. My kids love it, Get it
Delightful. This earns a spot in the short list of demos for friends who have never seen VR... and I've watched it a few times just for a little mood boost.

review_title: A fun little cartoon music video
one_reviews_text: Like the song. Simple cartoon animation. Worth 99c to bring a smile to your face but no more.
Nice addition to my library. Great warm up song to get the heart puming. The price is just right... Dev team, please do more! :)
Play this when you're feeling down and you'll find yourself smiling and dancing. Love it - one of the first things I show VR noobs now.
This wasn't really my taste, but it will probably appeal to a lot of viewers.
Was feeling a bit down about getting owned by a kid over and over again in Landfall. Then i did this. much better. Well done 12 year old kid. well done.
Made me smile
Fun characters, brilliant animations, engaging and silly visuals and all tied together with a song from a band I love.
